-- Stability of the Euro Should Be the ECB’s Top Priority, Issing Tells Focus
-- B y   R a j i v   S e k h r i
-- 2012-01-06T05:31:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/stability-of-the-euro-should-be-the-ecb-s-top-priority-issing-tells-focus.html
Former European Central Bank Chief
Economist  Otmar Issing  said the stability of the euro needs to
be the top priority of the central bank, Focus magazine reported
today, citing an interview with him.  Issing said the euro “was and is a success”, adding that
the ECB’s priority should not be “financing national deficits
by purchasing national debt.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rajiv Sekhri at 
 rsekhri1@bloomberg.net  